td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Computer Languages:</td>\r\n<td>HTML, CSS, PHP, Javascript, Processing, Python</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Frameworks of Choice:</td>\r\n<td>Wordpress and Jquery. A LOT of Wordpress and Jquery.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2013-02-18 01:19:31','2013-02-18 01:19:31','',4,'http://thejsj.com/uncategorized/4-revision-83/',0,'revision','',0),(1305,1,'2013-03-23 20:48:47','0000-00-00 00:00:00','There seems to be an irreconcilable misunderstanding between the people we aspire to be and our current selves. We feel comfortable with our current selves and yet aspire to improve upon our condition. Our hopes and desires make us who we are, yet at the same time limits us to who we currently are.\r\n\r\nTaking the leap into the unexpected frightens us.\r\n\r\nStaying as we are leaves us only with dissatisfaction.\r\n\r\nI guess I\'ve decided I\'ll be taking the side of the bad guys. I get bored with my current self and put myself to sleep with the idea that tomorrow it will be better, that tomorrow I will do something about it. I have many times, done something about it, but I need to keep doing them. The distance between who I was yesterday and who I want to become tomorrow scares me. The more wildly exciting the future becomes, the greater the distance to who you formerly were.\r\n\r\nAm I o.k. with that distance?\r\n\r\nTheoretically, rationally, logically, I want to take the greatest leaps I possibly can. I don\'t want to be scared. I know everything is going to be fine. But, emotionally, I am. I cling to my former selves, but I still want more.\r\n\r\nIt happens one day at time, hour by hour, minute by minute. It all goes by so quickly, so slowly. It seems possible at every second, you just need to start.','Clinging','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-03-23 20:48:47','2013-03-23 20:48:47','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?p=1305',0,'post','',0),(1277,1,'2013-02-18 21:15:42','20