d be stopped and removed. You can check out the code in <a href=\"https://github.com/thejsj/AnythingWorthSaying-Exhibition\">Github</a>.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"1357,1358,1359,1360,1361,1362,1363,1364\"]\r\n\r\nThis are some screenshots about the interactive part of the installation. Videos hover across the screen as to not impose a specific hierarchy.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"1372,1371,1370,1369,1368,1367,1366\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Anything Worth Saying - Exhibition','This was MFA exhibition, held last May. The exhibition consisted of three computers. The first one shows the videos in the database in random order. The second one is interactive, meant for users to choose which videos to watch. The third one is a recording station, meant for users to record their own videos. When users record their videos, these automatically shows up in the first computer and are added to the list of videos being displayed on the second computer. In this way, users can interact with the installation and add to the project their own content to the project.','inherit','open','open','','1356-revision-v1','','','2014-01-22 02:58:06','2014-01-22 02:58:06','',1356,'http://localhost/~jorgesilva/2014/thejsj9/?p=1636',0,'revision','',0),(1637,1,'2013-02-19 18:27:25','2013-02-19 18:27:25','<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Poster-Design-Inquiry-JSJ.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-1285\" alt=\"Poster - Design Inquiry - JSJ\" src=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Poster-Design-Inquiry-JSJ-768x1024.jpg\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSome Details:\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"1282,1281,1283,1280\"]\r\n\r\nSome Interesting photos from the shooting:\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"1288,1289,1291,1292,1293,1294,1295,1296\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Design Inquiry Poster','','inherit','open','open','','1286-revision-v1','','','2013-02-19 18:27:25','2013