er, currently pursuing an MFA from Virginia Commonwealth University in Richmond, Virginia.\r\n\r\nThis is a corner of the web solely dedicated to show some of my work. This is a very simple site, but with some interesting twists.The work in this site range from some very simple designs, to some experimental explorations, to some complex programming on some pieces. Some of the work is for clients, some is personal, most is for my MFA and some is NGO\'s and non-profits.!!!\r\n<h3>You can get in touch with me at</h3>\r\njorge.silva [ at ] thejsj.com\r\n<h3>You can view my <a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/CV-Resume-Jorge-Silva-Jetter.pdf\">curriculum vitae</a>.</h3>\r\nQuite honestly, I prefer Latin over French. Désolé à tous les Français.\r\n<h3>Some Facts</h3>\r\n<table id=\"facts\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Name:</td>\r\n<td>Jorge R. Silva Jetter</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Lives in:</td>\r\n<td>Richmond, VA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>From:</td>\r\n<td>San Juan, Puerto Rico</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Studied at:</td>\r\n<td>University of Puerto Rico (Psychology)\r\nVirginia Commonwealth University (MFA in Visual Communications)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Human Languages:</td>\r\n<td>Spanish (Native), English (Excellent), Portuguese (Good), French (Basic)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Computer Languages:</td>\r\n<td>HTML, CSS, Javascript, PHP, Python, <a title=\"Processing\" href=\"http://processing.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Processing</a>, <a title=\"SASS\" href=\"http://sass-lang.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SASS</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Frameworks of Choice:</td>\r\n<td>Wordpress and Jquery. A LOT of Wordpress and Jquery.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2014-02-05 04:59:46','2014-02-05 04:59:46','',4,'http://thejsj.com/uncategorized/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1772,1,'2014-02-05 05:29:19','2014-02-05 05:29:19','Hi. My name is Jorge Silva. I am developer/designer based in Richmond, VA. During the day, I work at <a href=\"http://www.teamcolab.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Co+Lab</a> as a Front-end/Backend developer. Yes, I\'m awesome at both. After the sun goes down, I make things I want to make like <a href=\"http://clickonjorge.com\" target=\"_blank\">interactive games</a>, <a href=\"http://npossibleroutes.info/\" target=\"_blank\">data visualization projects</a> and <a title=\"JSJ Gallery Slideshow\" href=\"http://thejsj.com/jsj-gallery-slideshow/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress plugins</a>.\r\n\r\nAs someone with a design background who got very interested in programming, I try not to define myself by the programming languages and frameworks I know and love. Instead, I\'m more interested in what I make and how I\'m able to creatively use technology. Maybe, I\'ve forgotten that lately.  All that being said, I usually work with Javascript, Jquery, Backbone, and Sass on the client side and with Worpress/PHP and Django/Python on the server side. Almost every project I take on has a significant integration of front-end and backend and I take great pride in being able to master both.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">I  really enjoy making things with urls. I like working in a medium where there are no physical limit to what you can do. I like working in a medium that is inherently public yet </span>strangely<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"> private and intimate. </span>\r\n\r\nI graduated with a Masters in Fine Art from <a href=\"http://arts.vcu.edu/graphicdesign/\" target=\"_blank\">Virginia Commonwealth University</a>, right here in Richmond. Before that, I studied Psychology at the University of Puerto Rico.','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2014-02-05 05:29:19','2014-02-05 05:29:19','',4,'http://thejsj.com/uncategorized/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1766,1,'2014-02-05 05:14:15','2014-02-05 05:14:15','Hi. My name is Jorge Silva. I am developer/designer based in Richmond, 